<component name="ApplyFEMVoltageSource" category="Forward">
  <overview>
    <authors>
      <author>David Weinstein</author>
    </authors>
    <summary>The module changes/creates the right-hand side (RHS) and 
    forward matrices for voltgage (Dirichlet) boundary conditions.</summary>
    <description>
      <p>Version Date: March 2001</p><p>Version: 1.0</p>
      <p>The module has the following behaviour:</p>
      <orderedlist>
	<listitem>
	  <p>When the module doesn't find ColumnMatrix on its imput
	  containing RHS to modify or the ColumnMatrix found is of
	  size different than the number of nodes in the mesh, it
	  creates a new ColumnMatrix and fills it in correspondence
	  with the supplied mesh and dipole parameters</p>
	</listitem>
	<listitem>
	  <p>The supplied mesh is assumed to be of type TetVolField(int)
	  containing indices to conductivity tensor lookup
	  table. Further requirements to the supplied mesh are
	  described in documentation to BioPSE::Forward::SetupFEMatrix 
	  module</p>
	</listitem>
      </orderedlist>
    </description>
  </overview>
  <io>
    <inputs lastportdynamic="no">
      <port>
	<name>Mesh</name>
	<description>
	  <p>FEM conductivity mesh</p>
	</description>
	<datatype>SCIRun::Field</datatype>
	<componentname>FieldReader</componentname>
      </port>
      <port>
	<name>Stiffness Matrix</name>
	<description>
	  <p>FEM Stiffness Matrix</p>
	</description>
	<datatype>SCIRun::Matrix</datatype>
	<componentname>MatrixReader</componentname>
      </port>
      <port>
	<name>RHS</name>
	<description>
	  <p>FEM Right Hand Side (b) Vector</p>
	</description>
	<datatype>SCIRun::Matrix</datatype>
	<componentname>MatrixReader</componentname>
      </port>
    </inputs>

    <outputs>
      <port>
	<name>Forward Matrix</name>
	<description>
	  <p>FEM Forward (A) Matrix</p>
	</description>
	<datatype>SCIRun::Matrix</datatype>
	<componentname>MatrixReader</componentname>
      </port>
      <port>
	<name>RHS</name>
	<description>
	  <p>FEM Right Hand Side (b) Vector</p>
	</description>
	<datatype>SCIRun::Matrix</datatype>
	<componentname>MatrixReader</componentname>
      </port>
    </outputs>
  </io>
  
  <testing>
  </testing>
</component>
